{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Legislate for Mobile Phones to have Hardware \"Kill Switch\" to help reduce thefts",
        "additional_details": "According to figures from the Metropolitan Police, 70,137 phones were stolen in London in 2024. \r\n \r\nMobile phone theft can cause dramatic trauma to the victim, and is a major crime wave. Information yielded from the phone can be used to fraudulently extort money from bank accounts, and the phones are reprogrammed and sold on the black market.",
        "background": "To legislate to require all mobile phones imported into, or manufactured in the UK, to have a Hardware Kill switch. This would prevent stolen phones from being accessed by the thieves. We believe current software security does not provide adequate protection.",
